# Shifting Payment Integration to Google Play Billing (via RevenueCat)

This plan outlines the migration from **Dodo Payments** (web checkout) to **Google Play Billing** (native Android In-App Purchases/Subscriptions) using **RevenueCat** as the subscription management platform.

Using RevenueCat allows us to handle receipt validation, subscription state changes, and webhook delivery reliably without writing a custom Google Play billing API wrapper.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **RevenueCat Dashboard Configuration Required**
> Before deploying this change, you will need to:
> 1. Set up a **Google Play Console Developer Account** and a **Merchant Account**.
> 2. Create your subscription products (`pro_monthly` and `advanced_monthly`) in the Google Play Console under **Monetization > Subscriptions**.
> 3. Create a **Google Cloud Service Account** with "Google Play Financial" or billing permissions, download its JSON key, and upload it to the **RevenueCat Dashboard**.
> 4. Add the **RevenueCat API Key** (`goog_...`) to your mobile app configuration.
> 5. Add a **RevenueCat Webhook Secret** (or authorization token) to your backend environment variables (`REVENUECAT_WEBHOOK_SECRET`) to secure the webhook endpoint.

